Third-Party Notices
===================

Hash Playground combines original Luau code with a few ports and adaptations
of public reference implementations for cryptographic algorithms.

Top-level repository license
============================
Unless otherwise noted, original project files are made available under the
Mozilla Public License 2.0. See LICENSE for the full text.

Per-file notes
==============
Original project files
- src/client/HashGUI.client.lua
- src/shared/CRCModule.lua
- src/shared/HMACModule.lua
- src/shared/SHA1Module.lua

Adapted or ported files
- src/shared/MD5Module.lua
  Ported from Zunawe/md5-c.
  Upstream license: Unlicense.
  This file is additionally made available under MPL-2.0 in this repository.

- src/shared/SHA256Module.lua
  Ported from the Brad Conte crypto-algorithms implementation.
  Upstream project README describes that code as public domain.

- src/shared/SHA512Module.lua
  Ported from the OpenSSL SHA-512 implementation.
  Upstream license: Apache License 2.0.

- src/shared/PBKDF2Module.lua
  Ported from the OpenSSL PBKDF2 implementation.
  Upstream license: Apache License 2.0.

- src/shared/SCOKeygenModule.lua
  Ported from the sb SCO serial utility.
  Upstream license: MIT.

- src/shared/BLAKE2bModule.lua
  Based on the BLAKE2 reference implementation family.
  The upstream reference package offers Apache 2.0 among its license options,
  which is the license chosen for this port.

- src/shared/BLAKE3Module.lua
  Based on the official BLAKE3 reference implementation family.
  The upstream project offers Apache 2.0 among its license options,
  which is the license chosen for this port.

